The paper deals with communication over channels, which is a topic covered in information theory (cs.IT). The use of sequential decoding suggests a focus on networking and communication systems (cs.NI). The mention of a sensor transmitting information to a remote base station suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY). The application of the results to antipodal signaling over a Gaussian channel suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the use of probability and statistics in analyzing the performance of the communication system suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG).
